OpenConfig working group
OpenConfig working group netopenconfig@googlegroups.com
This module defines configuration and state variables for VLANs, in addition to VLAN parameters associated with interfaces.
Fix bug with name of 802.1ad identity.
Move top-level vlan data to network-instance; Update identities to comply to style guide; fixed pattern quoting; corrected trunk vlan types; added TPID config to base interface.

Adds VLAN settings to individual Ethernet interfaces
oc-if:type = 'ift:ethernetCsmacd'
Active when the interface is Ethernet
Enclosing container for VLAN interface-specific data on Ethernet interfaces. These are for standard L2, switched-style VLANs.
Configuration parameters for VLANs
interface-mode = 'TRUNK'
Allowed VLANs may be specified for trunk mode interfaces.

Specify VLANs, or ranges thereof, that the interface may carry when in trunk mode. If not specified, all VLANs are allowed on the interface. Ranges are specified in the form x..y, where x<y - ranges are assumed to be inclusive (such that the VLAN range is x <= range <= y.
Set the interface to access or trunk mode for VLANs
interface-mode = 'TRUNK'
Native VLAN is valid for trunk mode interfaces

Set the native VLAN id for untagged frames arriving on a trunk interface. Tagged frames sent on an interface configured with a native VLAN should have their tags stripped prior to transmission. This configuration is only valid on a trunk interface.
interface-mode = 'ACCESS'
Access VLAN assigned to the interfaces
Assign the access vlan to the access port.
